      "hash": "d92f24e8a0952ae657c3e6810141dcec02316d1d",
      "heading": "Applications for Insert Molding",
      "level": "h3",
      "text": "Applications for Insert Molding End-Use Functional Parts Insertion molding creates fully dense, smooth parts with superior mechanical performance. Scaled Production Insert injection molding is best known for its unmatched production capabilities from thousands to millions of identical parts. Certified Components We offer ISO 9001, AS9100, ISO 13485, UL, ITAR, and ISO 7 & 8 Medical Clean Room molding."
    },
    {
      "hash": "a93dd4e74d419ed012fbb16d9e915cf50928f873",
      "heading": "Insert Molding Process Advantages",
      "level": "h3",
      "text": "Insert Molding Process Advantages Durability: Metal inserts will guarantee the function of threads and mitigate wear and tear over the partâs life. Strength: Because itâs a âone-shotâ process, insert molding can produce stronger parts than overmolding and other processes. Creating Production Parts: Insert molding is great for creating prototypes and production parts."
    },
